name: Peacock butterfly
description:
This butterfly collages is part of a series of three. Each one features a  butterfly from a different part of the world; this one is of a Peacock butterfly. Behind each butterfly is a map of where it comes from. The collages also incorporate piano music (Chopin), which to me mirrors the musical patterns I see in their flight. Each piece also features an image of an electrical transformer, since butterflies are commonly regarded as a symbol of transformation.

This reproduction measures 10" x 10" (each image is 8" x 8"). The image is printed on heavy card stock, mailed flat between two pieces of cardboard for protection.

name: Three butterflies
description:
I created these butterfly collages as a series. Each one features a  butterfly from a different part of the world. Behind each butterfly is a map of that region. The collages also incorporate piano music (Chopin), which to me mirrors the musical patterns I see in their flight. Each piece also features an image of an electrical transformer, since butterflies are commonly regarded as a symbol of transformation.

This reproduction of the series of three butterfly collages measures 10" x 28" (each image is 8" x 8"). The images are printed on heavy card stock, which  can be mailed flat or rolled.

name: Collage greeting card - heart
description: Each card features an original collage in the shape of a heart, created by Robi Smith. The collages are made by hand using upcycled materials such as maps, stamps, old recipes and labels. These unique cards are 7 x 5 inches, signed by the artist, blank inside, and come with a matching envelope. No two are exactly the same.

name: Barred Owl
description:
Original, signed 4-colour linocut print of a barred owl. Because linocut prints are individually made, each one is slightly different. This print is made in a limited edition of 80.

The size of the print is 7 x 5 inches. Each print is hand inked and pressed onto archival quality 100% cotton rag paper, and then signed by the artist. You have the choice of purchasing a matted print, or a matted print in an 8 x 10 inch white frame.

name: When I went for a walk today
description:
Go outside for a walk and see what you can see! Bring this journal along and draw as you go or collect things and stories on your walk and draw them when you get home. Each page starts with the words, "when I went for a walk today, I found..." You fill in the rest in words and/or pictures.

Printed locally on heavy 100% post-consumer recycled paper, perfect for writing and drawing. Coil bound. 21 pages, enough for 3 weeks of walks.

name: Last night I dreamed...
description:
Capture your dreams: colours, feelings, sounds, symbols, or the whole movie from start to finish. Invent new ones. Extend your dream state into your waking hours and discover yourself. 

Printed locally on heavy 100% post-consumer recycled paper, perfect for writing and drawing. Coil bound. 21 pages, or 3 weeks of dreams.

name: The Things I See
description:
This journal is for anyone who wants to draw something, but can’t remember what. Each page offers a nudge to observe, remember or imagine a different perspective on the world, with lots of space to write, draw, paint, and more. 

Printed locally on heavy 100% post-consumer recycled paper. Coil bound. 21 pages.

name: Fish of BC Colouring Book
description:
Children love to learn about 12 of BC’s more unusual fish and let their imaginations run wild as they colour them.

Each page features a different marine or freshwater fish, plus a few interesting facts about the fish and its habitat. 

Printed locally in Vancouver, BC, on heavy 100% post consumer recycled paper. 14 pages. Coil bound.

name: Leo - A Fairytale
description:
This little book is a fairytale about the Alberta Tar Sands, with a happy ending.

Leo is a little boy who lives in a village on the edge of the tar sands. He is called to go on a quest to save his mother, who is very ill. Along the way, he meets animals in the shrinking Boreal forest who provide him with a magic elixir. 

Printed in colour in booklet format. 8 pages. Written and illustrated by Robi Smith.

name: Collage greeting card - small
description: Each card features a unique collage made by Robi Smith. The collages are handmade using original maps, stamps, and other found paper ephemera, stuck to the card with eco-friendly glue. The cards are signed, blank inside, and come with their own matching envelope. The card stock is 100% cotton rag from Italy. Size is 3.5 x 5 inches.

name: Dragonfly
description:
